</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1628,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Variability.</emphasis>
One of the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[659,713,1629,1652]" name="Laos" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Laos</collectingCountry>
is somewhat smaller and has a slightly larger transparent cell between forewing Cu1 and Cu2. It also lacks the lines of scales extending from the outer margin of the forewing termen into each of the cells. However, we believe that these small differences reflect intraspecific variation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="597" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,1735,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Habitat and Biology.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[505,603,1735,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">holotype</typeStatus>
and one 
<typeStatus box="[706,802,1736,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">paratype</typeStatus>
were collected on the banks of a small river surrounded by secondary tropical rainforest (
<figureCitation box="[526,596,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[194,1395,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Aschistophleps species and habitat. 1. A. ignisquamulata spec. nov., holotype, Thailand. 2. A. cucphuonganae comb. nov., Vietnam. 3. A. ignisquamulata spec. nov., paratype, male genitalia. 4. Type locality of A. ignisquamulata spec. nov. in Thailand." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444384/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). One specimen was attracted to artificial pheromone lures between 9 and 11.30 am. Another specimen was found sucking moisture from damp sand near the river. This ‘mud-puddling’ behaviour has been described for several species of the genera 
<taxonomicName authority=", Heterospecia Le Cerf, 1916" authorityName=", Heterospecia Le Cerf" authorityYear="1916" box="[882,1386,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Aschistophleps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[882,1050,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Aschistophleps</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1066,1215,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Heterospecia</emphasis>
Le Cerf, 1916
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorbunov &amp; Arita, 1995" authorityName="Gorbunov &amp; Arita" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,587,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Akaisphecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Akaisphecia</emphasis>
Gorbunov &amp; Arita, 1995
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[605,791,1879,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" refId="ref2343" refString="Gorbunov, O. G. (2015) Scientific Note: Clearwing moths (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) of Laos. I. Akaisphecia melanopuncta O. Gorbunov &amp; Arita, 1995 (Sesiidae: Sesiinae: Osminiini). Tropical Lepidoptera Research, 25 (2), 98 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2018.02.002" type="journal article">Gorbunov 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[806,977,1879,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" refId="ref2594" refString="Skowron, M. A., Munisamy, B., Hamid, S. B. &amp; wegrzyn, G. (2015) A new species of clearwing moth (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae: Osminiini) from Peninsular Malaysia, exhibiting bee-like morphology and behaviour. Zootaxa, 4032 (4), 426 - 434. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4032.4.7" type="journal article">Skowron 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[991,1405,1879,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" refId="ref2666" refString="Skowron Volponi, M. A. &amp; Volponi, P. (2017 a) A new species of wasp-mimicking clearwing moth from Peninsular Malaysia with DNA barcode and behavioural notes (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae). Zookeys, 692, 129 - 139. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 692.13587" type="journal article">Skowron Volponi &amp; Volponi 2017a</bibRefCitation>
– 
<bibRefCitation box="[1420,1432,1880,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" refId="ref2795" refString="Skowron Volponi, M. A. &amp; Volponi, P. (2017 c) A new species of bee-mimicking clearwing moth (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Thailand, with description and video of its behaviour. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 21, 279 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2017.12.007" type="journal article">c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,209,1916,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" refId="ref2859" refString="Skowron Volponi, M. A., McLean, D. J., Volponi, P. &amp; Dudley, R. (2018) Moving like a model: mimicry of hymenopteran flight trajectories by clearwing moths of Southeast Asian rainforests. Biological Letters, 14, 20180152. https: // doi. org / 10.1098 / rsbl. 2018.0152" type="journal article">2018</bibRefCitation>
) and may be a trait typical of Oriental 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duckworth &amp; Eichlin" authorityYear="1977" box="[643,759,1916,1941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sesiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Osminiini">Osminiini</taxonomicName>
. The hostplant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kallies &amp; Štolc" authorityYear="2018" box="[959,1165,1916,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Aschistophleps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignisquamulata">
<emphasis box="[959,1165,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">A. ignisquamulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1115,1952,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1977]" box="[199,1115,1952,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1952,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Etymology.</emphasis>
